Allow Tab and Shift+Tab to navigate the item list by directly calling
commandStack.currentItem.moveDown() / moveUp(), matching the same pattern
used by the Up/Down arrow keys in the SearchBar QML.

Tab is intercepted by Qt's QML focus navigation system before it reaches
the C++ eventFilter or the action binding system. The Up/Down arrows
bypass this by calling moveDown/moveUp directly in QML — Tab should do
the same.

Note: the launcher.forwardKey() fallback in Keys.onPressed does not work
for bare Tab because activateBoundAction never matches user-configured
keybind shortcuts (they use a different registration path).

Keys.onBacktabPressed is changed to accept the event so Backtab can
reach Keys.onPressed where we handle it alongside Tab.

diff --git a/src/server/src/qml/qml/SearchBar.qml b/src/server/src/qml/qml/SearchBar.qml
index 16be339..c328237 100644
--- a/src/server/src/qml/qml/SearchBar.qml
+++ b/src/server/src/qml/qml/SearchBar.qml
@@ -198,7 +198,7 @@ Item {
                 Keys.onBacktabPressed: event => {
-                    event.accepted = false;
+                    event.accepted = true;
                 }
                 Keys.onPressed: event => {
                     if (_handleEmacsEditing(event)) {
                         event.accepted = true;
+                    } else if (event.key === Qt.Key_Tab || event.key === Qt.Key_Backtab) {
+                        // Tab/Shift+Tab navigate the item list (dmenu/rofi style).
+                        // Direct inline call mirrors Up/Down arrow handling.
+                        const nav = typeof commandStack.currentItem.moveDown === "function";
+                        if (nav && event.key === Qt.Key_Tab) {
+                            event.accepted = commandStack.currentItem.moveDown();
+                        } else if (nav && event.key === Qt.Key_Backtab) {
+                            event.accepted = commandStack.currentItem.moveUp();
+                        } else {
+                            event.accepted = launcher.forwardKey(event.key, event.modifiers);
+                        }
                     } else if (_handleNavigation(event)) {
                         event.accepted = true;
